Flags are local toggles that enable or disable behaviour in my version-
controlled .vimrc.  The flags themselves are not version-controlled.

Flags allow me to distribute a collection of predefined behaviours to my login
environments while reserving the right to easily opt-out of behaviours where it
makes sense to do so.

To assert a flag, touch a regular file in this directory named after the flag.


Supported flags
===============

disable-vundle:

  Vundle (Vim plug-in manager) is enabled by default.  Assert this flag to
  disable Vundle and *all* Vundle plugins.

enable-color-base16

enable-color-solarized

enable-modelines

enable-syntastic

enable-vim-outliner

enable-youcompleteme

enable-lang-clojure

enable-lang-coffeescript

enable-lang-markdown

enable-lang-puppet
